The paper discusses intrusion detection in industrial networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Matrix Profiles for detecting outliers in time series data suggests a focus on network analysis and anomaly detection (cs.NE). The proposed integration concept for both methods involves machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The detection of anomalous communication patterns using graph representations suggests a focus on network science and social network analysis (cs.SI). Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms for motif discovery and outlier detection suggests a focus on machine learning and data mining (cs.LG).
